name: Acquirer Identifier
desc: Uniquely identifies the acquirer within each payment system

name: Additional Terminal Capabilities
desc: Indicates the data input and output capabilities of the terminal

name: Amount, Authorised (Binary)
desc: Authorised amount of the transaction (excluding adjustments)

name: Amount, Authorised (Numeric)
desc: Authorised amount of the transaction (excluding adjustments)

name: Amount, Other (Binary)
desc: Secondary amount associated with the transaction representing a cashback amount

name: Amount, Other (Numeric)
desc: Secondary amount associated with the transaction representing a cashback amount

name: Amount, Reference Currency
desc: Authorised amount expressed in the reference currency

name: Application Cryptogram
desc: Cryptogram returned by the ICC in response of the GENERATE AC command

name: Application Currency Code
desc: Indicates the currency in which the account is managed according to ISO 4217

name: Application Currency Exponent
desc: Indicates the implied position of the decimal point from the right of the amount represented according to ISO 4217

name: Application Discretionary Data
desc: Issuer or payment system specified data relating to the application

name: Application Effective Date
desc: Date from which the application may be used

name: Application Expiration Date
desc: Date after which application expires

name: Application File Locator (AFL)
desc: Indicates the location (SFI, range of records) of the AEFs related to a given application

name: Application Identifier (AID) – card
desc: Identifies the application as described in ISO/IEC 7816-5

name: Application Identifier (AID) – terminal
desc: Identifies the application as described in ISO/IEC 7816-5

name: Application Interchange Profile
desc: Indicates the capabilities of the card to support specific functions in the application

name: Application Label
desc: Mnemonic associated with the AID according to ISO/IEC 7816-5

name: Application Preferred Name
desc: Preferred mnemonic associated with the AID

name: Application Primary Account Number (PAN)
desc: Valid cardholder account number

name: Application Primary Account Number (PAN) Sequence Number
desc: Identifies and differentiates cards with the same PAN

name: Application Priority Indicator
desc: Indicates the priority of a given application or group of applications in a directory

name: Application Reference Currency
desc: 1–4 currency codes used between the terminal and the ICC when the Transaction Currency Code is different from the Application Currency Code; each code is 3 digits according to ISO 4217

name: Application Reference Currency Exponent
desc: Indicates the implied position of the decimal point from the right of the amount, for each of the 1–4 reference currencies represented according to ISO 4217

name: Application Selection Indicator
desc:
For an application in the ICC to be supported by an application in the terminal, the Application Selection Indicator indicates whether the associated AID in the terminal must match the AID in the card exactly, including the length of the AID, or only up to the length of the AID in the terminal

There is only one Application Selection Indicator per AID supported by the terminal

name: Application Template
desc: Contains one or more data objects relevant to an application directory entry according to ISO/IEC 7816-5

name: Application Transaction Counter (ATC)
desc: Counter maintained by the application in the ICC (incrementing the ATC is managed by the ICC)

name: Application Usage Control
desc: Indicates issuer’s specified restrictions on the geographic usage and services allowed for the application

name: Application Version Number
desc: Version number assigned by the payment system for the application

name: Application Version Number
desc: Version number assigned by the payment system for the application

name: Authorisation Code
desc: Value generated by the authorisation authority for an approved transaction

name: Authorisation Response Code
desc: Code that defines the disposition of a message

name: Authorisation Response Cryptogram (ARPC)
desc: Cryptogram generated by the issuer and used by the card to verify that the response came from the issuer.

name: Bank Identifier Code (BIC)
desc: Uniquely identifies a bank as defined in ISO 9362.

name: Card Risk Management Data Object List 1 (CDOL1)
desc: List of data objects (tag and length) to be passed to the ICC in the first GENERATE AC command

name: Card Risk Management Data Object List 2 (CDOL2)
desc: List of data objects (tag and length) to be passed to the ICC in the second GENERATE AC command

name: Card Status Update (CSU)
desc: Contains data sent to the ICC to indicate whether the issuer approves or declines the transaction, and to initiate actions specified by the issuer. Transmitted to the card in Issuer Authentication Data.

name: Cardholder Name
desc: Indicates cardholder name according to ISO 7813

name: Cardholder Name Extended
desc: Indicates the whole cardholder name when greater than 26 characters using the same coding convention as in ISO 7813

name: Cardholder Verification Method (CVM) List
desc: Identifies a method of verification of the cardholder supported by the application

name: Cardholder Verification Method (CVM) Results
desc: Indicates the results of the last CVM performed

name: Certification Authority Public Key Check Sum
desc: A check value calculated on the concatenation of all parts of the Certification Authority Public Key (RID, Certification Authority Public Key Index, Certification Authority Public Key Modulus, Certification Authority Public Key Exponent) using SHA-1

name: Certification Authority Public Key Exponent
desc: Value of the exponent part of the Certification Authority Public Key

name: Certification Authority Public Key Index
desc: Identifies the certification authority’s public key in conjunction with the RID

name: Certification Authority Public Key Index
desc: Identifies the certification authority’s public key in conjunction with the RID

name: Certification Authority Public Key Modulus
desc: Value of the modulus part of the Certification Authority Public Key

name: Command Template
desc: Identifies the data field of a command message

name: Cryptogram Information Data
desc: Indicates the type of cryptogram and the actions to be performed by the terminal

name: Data Authentication Code
desc: An issuer assigned value that is retained by the terminal during the verification process of the Signed Static Application Data

name: Dedicated File (DF) Name
desc: Identifies the name of the DF as described in ISO/IEC 7816-4

name: Default Dynamic Data Authentication Data Object List (DDOL)
desc: DDOL to be used for constructing the INTERNAL AUTHENTICATE command if the DDOL in the card is not present

name: Default Transaction Certificate Data Object List (TDOL)
desc: TDOL to be used for generating the TC Hash Value if the TDOL in the card is not present

name: Directory Definition File (DDF) Name
desc: Identifies the name of a DF associated with a directory

name: Directory Discretionary Template
desc: Issuer discretionary part of the directory according to ISO/IEC 7816-5

name: Dynamic Data Authentication Data Object List (DDOL)
desc: List of data objects (tag and length) to be passed to the ICC in the INTERNAL AUTHENTICATE command

name: EMV Proprietary Template
desc: Template proprietary to the EMV specification

name: Enciphered Personal Identification Number (PIN) Data
desc: Transaction PIN enciphered at the PIN pad for online verification or for offline verification if the PIN pad and IFD are not a single integrated device

name: File Control Information (FCI) Issuer Discretionary Data
desc: Issuer discretionary part of the FCI

name: File Control Information (FCI) Proprietary Template
desc: Identifies the data object proprietary to this specification in the FCI template according to ISO/IEC 7816-4

name: File Control Information (FCI) Template
desc: Identifies the FCI template according to ISO/IEC 7816-4

name: ICC Dynamic Number
desc: Time-variant number generated by the ICC, to be captured by the terminal

name: Integrated Circuit Card (ICC) PIN Encipherment Public Key Certificate
desc: ICC PIN Encipherment Public Key certified by the issuer

name: Integrated Circuit Card (ICC) PIN Encipherment Public Key Exponent
desc: ICC PIN Encipherment Public Key Exponent used for PIN encipherment

name: Integrated Circuit Card (ICC) PIN Encipherment Public Key Remainder
desc: Remaining digits of the ICC PIN Encipherment Public Key Modulus

name: Integrated Circuit Card (ICC) Public Key Certificate
desc: ICC Public Key certified by the issuer

name: Integrated Circuit Card (ICC) Public Key Exponent
desc: ICC Public Key Exponent used for the verification of the Signed Dynamic Application Data

name: Integrated Circuit Card (ICC) Public Key Remainder
desc: Remaining digits of the ICC Public Key Modulus

name: Interface Device (IFD) Serial Number
desc: Unique and permanent serial number assigned to the IFD by the manufacturer

name: International Bank Account Number (IBAN)
desc: Uniquely identifies the account of a customer at a financial institution as defined in ISO 13616.

name: Issuer Action Code – Default
desc: Specifies the issuer’s conditions that cause a transaction to be rejected if it might have been approved online, but the terminal is unable to process the transaction online

name: Issuer Action Code – Denial
desc: Specifies the issuer’s conditions that cause the denial of a transaction without attempt to go online

name: Issuer Action Code – Online
desc: Specifies the issuer’s conditions that cause a transaction to be transmitted online

name: Issuer Application Data
desc: Contains proprietary application data for transmission to the issuer in an online transaction

name: Issuer Authentication Data
desc: Data sent to the ICC for online issuer authentication

name: Issuer Code Table Index
desc: Indicates the code table according to ISO/IEC 8859 for displaying the Application Preferred Name

name: Issuer Country Code
desc: Indicates the country of the issuer according to ISO 3166

name: Issuer Country Code (alpha2 format)
desc: Indicates the country of the issuer as defined in ISO 3166 (using a 2 character alphabetic code)

name: Issuer Country Code (alpha3 format)
desc: Indicates the country of the issuer as defined in ISO 3166 (using a 3 character alphabetic code)

name: Issuer Identification Number (IIN)
desc: The number that identifies the major industry and the card issuer and that forms the first part of the Primary Account Number (PAN)

name: Issuer Public Key Certificate
desc: Issuer public key certified by a certification authority

name: Issuer Public Key Exponent
desc: Issuer public key exponent used for theverification of the Signed Static Application Data and the ICC Public Key Certificate

name: Issuer Public Key Remainder
desc: Remaining digits of the Issuer Public Key Modulus

name: Issuer Script Command
desc: Contains a command for transmission to the ICC

name: Issuer Script Identifier
desc: Identification of the Issuer Script

name: Issuer Script Results
desc: Indicates the result of the terminal script processing

name: Issuer Script Template 1
desc: Contains proprietary issuer data for transmission to the ICC before the second GENERATE AC command

name: Issuer Script Template 2
desc: Contains proprietary issuer data for transmission to the ICC after the second GENERATE AC command

name: Issuer URL
desc: The URL provides the location of the Issuer’s Library Server on the Internet.

name: Language Preference
desc:
1–4 languages stored in order of preference, each represented by 2 alphabetical characters according to ISO 639

Note: EMVCo strongly recommends that cards be personalised with data element '5F2D' coded in lowercase, but that terminals accept the data element whether it is coded in upper or lower case.

name: Last Online Application Transaction Counter (ATC) Register
desc: ATC value of the last transaction that went online

name: Log Entry
desc: Provides the SFI of the Transaction Log file and its number of records

name: Log Format
desc: List (in tag and length format) of data objects representing the logged data elements that are passed to the terminal when a transaction log record is read

name: Lower Consecutive Offline Limit
desc: Issuer-specified preference for the maximum number of consecutive offline transactions for this ICC application allowed in a terminal with online capability

name: Maximum Target Percentage to be used for Biased Random Selection
desc: Value used in terminal risk management for random transaction selection

name: Merchant Category Code
desc: Classifies the type of business being done by the merchant, represented according to ISO 8583:1993 for Card Acceptor Business Code

name: Merchant Identifier
desc: When concatenated with the Acquirer Identifier, uniquely identifies a given merchant

name: Merchant Name and Location
desc: Indicates the name and location of the merchant

name: Message Type
desc: Indicates whether the batch data capture record is a financial record or advice

name: Personal Identification Number (PIN) Pad Secret Key
desc: Secret key of a symmetric algorithm used by the PIN pad to encipher the PIN and by the card reader to decipher the PIN if the PIN pad and card reader are not integrated

name: Personal Identification Number (PIN) Try Counter
desc: Number of PIN tries remaining

name: Point-of-Service (POS) Entry Mode
desc: Indicates the method by which the PAN was entered, according to the first two digits of the ISO 8583:1987 POS Entry Mode

name: Processing Options Data Object List (PDOL)
desc: Contains a list of terminal resident data objects (tags and lengths) needed by the ICC in processing the GET PROCESSING OPTIONS command

name: Proprietary Authentication Data
desc:
Contains issuer data for transmission to the card in the Issuer Authentication Data of an online transaction.

For a cryptogram defined by the Common Core Definitions with a Cryptogram Version of '4', the Proprietary Authentication Data element shall be 0 bytes long. The only Cryptogram Version currently defined for the Common Core Definitions is '4'.

name: Response Message Template Format 1
desc: Contains the data objects (without tags and lengths) returned by the ICC in response to a command

name: Response Message Template Format 2
desc: Contains the data objects (with tags and lengths) returned by the ICC in response to a command

name: Service Code
desc: Service code as defined in ISO/IEC 7813 for track 1 and track 2

name: Short File Identifier (SFI)
desc: Identifies the SFI to be used in the commands related to a given AEF or DDF. The SFI data object is a binary field with the three high order bits set to zero.

name: Signed Dynamic Application Data
desc: Digital signature on critical application parameters for DDA or CDA

name: Signed Static Application Data
desc: Digital signature on critical application parameters for SDA

name: Static Data Authentication Tag List
desc: List of tags of primitive data objects defined in this specification whose value fields are to be included in the Signed Static or Dynamic Application Data

name: Target Percentage to be Used for Random Selection
desc: Value used in terminal risk management for random transaction selection

name: Terminal Action Code – Default
desc: Specifies the acquirer’s conditions that cause a transaction to be rejected if it might have been approved online, but the terminal is unable to process the transaction online

name: Terminal Action Code – Denial
desc: Specifies the acquirer’s conditions that cause the denial of a transaction without attempt to go online

name: Terminal Action Code – Online
desc: Specifies the acquirer’s conditions that cause a transaction to be transmitted online

name: Terminal Capabilities
desc: Indicates the card data input, CVM, and security capabilities of the terminal

name: Terminal Country Code
desc: Indicates the country of the terminal, represented according to ISO 3166

name: Terminal Floor Limit
desc: Indicates the floor limit in the terminal in conjunction with the AID

name: Terminal Identification
desc: Designates the unique location of a terminal at a merchant

name: Terminal Risk Management Data
desc: Application-specific value used by the card for risk management purposes

name: Terminal Type
desc: Indicates the environment of the terminal, its communications capability, and its operational control

name: Terminal Verification Results
desc: Status of the different functions as seen from the terminal

name: Threshold Value for Biased Random Selection
desc: Value used in terminal risk management for random transaction selection

name: Track 1 Discretionary Data
desc: Discretionary part of track 1 according to ISO/IEC 7813

name: Track 2 Discretionary Data
desc: Discretionary part of track 2 according to ISO/IEC 7813

name: Track 2 Equivalent Data
desc:
Contains the data elements of track 2 according to ISO/IEC 7813, excluding start sentinel, end sentinel, and Longitudinal Redundancy Check (LRC), as follows:

Primary Account Number (n, var. up to 19)
Field Separator (Hex 'D') (b)
Expiration Date (YYMM) (n 4)
Service Code (n 3)
Discretionary Data (defined by individual payment systems) (n, var.)
Pad with one Hex 'F' if needed to ensure whole bytes (b)

name: Transaction Amount
desc: Clearing amount of the transaction, including tips and other adjustments

name: Transaction Certificate (TC) Hash Value
desc: Result of a hash function specified in Book 2, Annex B3.1

name: Transaction Certificate Data Object List (TDOL)
desc: List of data objects (tag and length) to be used by the terminal in generating the TC Hash Value

name: Transaction Currency Code
desc: Indicates the currency code of the transaction according to ISO 4217

name: Transaction Currency Exponent
desc: Indicates the implied position of the decimal point from the right of the transaction amount represented according to ISO 4217

name: Transaction Date
desc: Local date that the transaction was authorised

name: Transaction Personal Identification Number (PIN) Data
desc: Data entered by the cardholder for the purpose of the PIN verification

name: Transaction Reference Currency Code
desc: Code defining the common currency used by the terminal in case the Transaction Currency Code is different from the Application Currency Code

name: Transaction Reference Currency Conversion
desc: Factor used in the conversion from the Transaction Currency Code to the Transaction Reference Currency Code

name: Transaction Reference Currency Exponent
desc: Indicates the implied position of the decimal point from the right of the transaction amount, with the Transaction Reference Currency Code represented according to ISO 4217

name: Transaction Sequence Counter
desc: Counter maintained by the terminal that is incremented by one for each transaction

name: Transaction Status Information
desc: Indicates the functions performed in a transaction

name: Transaction Time
desc: Local time that the transaction was authorised

name: Transaction Type
desc: Indicates the type of financial transaction, represented by the first two digits of ISO 8583:1987 Processing Code

name: Unpredictable Number
desc: Value to provide variability and uniqueness to the generation of a cryptogram

name: Upper Consecutive Offline Limit
desc: Issuer-specified preference for the maximum number of consecutive offline transactions for this ICC application allowed in a terminal without online capability
